The executive chairman of the Kano Internal Revenue Service Alhaji Sank Abdulkadir Dambo has resigned. In a letter dated 9th April 2020 addressed to the secretary to the state government Alhaji Usman Alhaji the chief executive thanked the governor for giving him the opportunity to serve. He did not specify reasons for his resignation in the letter however sources told our correspondent that his early resignation may not be unconnected to the report of his possible sack by the governor. It is not clear when a new executive chairman will be appointed but the sources confirmed the governor’s readiness to accept the resignation.